response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Sum of Odd Numbers\", \"description\": \"Given a list of integers, return the sum of all odd numbers in the list.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sum_odd_numbers(numbers: list[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `numbers` (list[int]): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of all odd numbers in the input list.\\n\", \"code\": \"\\ndef sum_odd_numbers(numbers: list[int]) -> int:\\n    total = 0\\n    for num in numbers:\\n        if num % 2 != 0:\\n            total += num\\n    return total\\n\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert sum_odd_numbers([1, 3, 5, 7, 9]) == 25\", \"assert sum_odd_numbers([2, 4, 6, 8, 10]) == 0\", \"assert sum_odd_numbers([-1, -3, -5, -7, -9]) == -20\"] }"
